01 - Basics
Exploring the basic foundations of Metasploit
Looked at different modules, commands, and how to navigate different modules. How to execute commands correctly in the metasploit framework eg. using modules, setting rhosts and rports etc

02 - Exploitation
Diving dseeper into scanning, exploiting, databases, and delivering payloads.
Expanded on scanning options, practiced some workflows in terminal / msfconsole
Demonstrated ability to exploit a machine and using meterpreter to gain flag and hasdumps
Created a payload and transfered it from attacking machine to target machine, executed it, and returned multiple user password hashes

03 - Meterpreter
An in-depth look at Meterpreter. The different useful commands we can use.
- Successfully exploited a virtual machine
- Checked machine system info
- Checked the shares, backgrounding session and using enum_shares module
- Identified PID and migrated to another PID. Hashdump revelaed NTLM hash of a user
- Converted hash to cleartext password of user
- Used search to find 2 secret files that contained sensitive information

04 - Blue
Using eternalblue exploit to gain access to sensitivbe information on a target machine
- Conducted Recon on the machine. Scanning for vulnerabilities
- Gain access to machine exploiting the ms17-010 vulnerability
- Escalated access by creating a shell to meterpreter session and migrating to an authority ran process
- Conducting a hashdump and cracking hash password to text
- Using shell, navigated around system to find 3 difffernt flags




